N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4226.14 - Matters to be referred to judges

State Regulations

For disobedience of his orders at the starting post or
for attempting any unfair advantage, the starter may refer the matter to the
judges for action; but any penalty shall not take effect until after the last
race of the day. Notes
